        <body>
            <div>
                <head>“TO A BROWN GIRL”</head>
                
                
                <lg>
                <lg type="quatrain">
                    <l enjamb="no">What if <rs theme="male">his</rs> glance is bold and <rhyme type="A">free.</rhyme></l>
                    <l enjamb="no"><rs theme="male">His</rs> mouth the lash of <rhyme type="B">whips?</rhyme></l>
                    <l enjamb="no">So should the eyes of <rs theme="love">lovers</rs><rhyme type="A">be,</rhyme></l>
                    <l enjamb="no">And so a <rs theme="love">lover's</rs><rhyme type="B">lips.</rhyme></l>
                </lg>
                </lg>
                
                <lg>
                <lg type="quatrain">
                    <l enjamb="no">What if no <rs theme="religion"> puritanic</rs><rhyme type="C">strain</rhyme></l>
                    <l enjamb="no">Confines <rs theme="male">him</rs> to the <rhyme type="D">nice?</rhyme></l>
                    <l enjamb="no"><rs theme="male">He</rs> will not pass this way <rhyme type="C">again</rhyme></l>
                    <l enjamb="no">Nor hunger for you <rhyme type="D">twice.</rhyme></l>
                </lg>
                </lg>
                
                <lg>
                <lg type="quatrain">
                    <l enjamb="no">Since in the end consort <rhyme type="E">together</rhyme></l>
                    <l enjamb="no"><name>Magdalen</name> and <name><rhyme type="F">Mary</rhyme></name>,</l>
                    <l enjamb="no">Youth is the time for <rs litDevice="personification">careless <rhyme type="E">weather;</rhyme></rs></l>
                    <l enjamb="no">Later, lass, be <rhyme type="F">wary.</rhyme></l>
                </lg>
                </lg>
                <byline>-Countée Cullen</byline>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
